.TH "Sdb" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
Sdb \- connection SequoiaDB object.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]var db = new Sdb([hostname],[svcname])\f[]
.PP
\f[B]var db = new Sdb([hostname],[svcname],[username],[password])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Sdb
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Create a Sdb object to connect to the SequoiaDB.
.SH PARAMETERS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]hostname\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Target hostname, default to be "localhost".
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]svcname\f[] ( \f[I]int\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Target svcname, default to be 11810.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]username\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[])
.PP
The username of the SequoiaDB user, if the SequoiaDB has no users.
default to be empty.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]password\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[] )
.PP
The password of the SequoiaDB user, if the SequoiaDB has no users.
default to be empty.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.RE
.RS
.IP "1." 3
Use createUsr() to create a user and set the password.
.RE
.RS
.IP "2." 3
If the SequoiaDB has users, then must use username and password to create the
Sdb object.
.RE
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, return an object of Sdb.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
The exceptions of \f[C]Sdb()\f[] are as below:
