.SH HISTORY
.PP
Since v1.12
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP "1." 3
Create a Sdb object connection to the SequoiaDB, hostname default to be
"localhost", svcname default to be 11810.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ var\ db\ =\ new\ Sdb()
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "2." 3
Create a Sdb object connection to the SequoiaDB on the specified host, target
hostname is "sdbserver1".
.nf
\f[C]
>\ var\ db\ =\ new\ Sdb("sdbserver1",11810)
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "3." 3
Create a Sdb object connection to the SequoiaDB on the specified host with a
username and password.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ var\ db\ =\ new\ Sdb("sdbserver1",11810,"admin","123")
\f[]
.fi
.RE
